From: conao3 <conao3@gmail.com>
Subject: codex/app_server: emit permissionMode on thread/start

Symphony's thread/start sends `approvalPolicy` (Codex-native), but
strict app-server implementations such as sapsaldog/claude-app-server
ignore that field and look at `permissionMode` instead. Without it,
the spawned `claude --print` runs with the default permission mode
and every tool call returns `turn/permission_denied`.

Map Symphony's `approval_policy: "never"` to claude's
`permissionMode: "bypassPermissions"` so the same `symphony` binary
can drive claude-app-server end-to-end. Codex's own app-server keeps
working because it reads `approvalPolicy` and ignores
`permissionMode`.

---
 lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex b/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
--- a/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
+++ b/lib/symphony_elixir/codex/app_server.ex
@@ -282,6 +282,7 @@ defmodule SymphonyElixir.Codex.AppServer do
       "id" => @thread_start_id,
       "params" => %{
         "approvalPolicy" => approval_policy,
+        "permissionMode" => if(approval_policy == "never", do: "bypassPermissions", else: "default"),
         "sandbox" => thread_sandbox,
         "cwd" => workspace,
         "dynamicTools" => DynamicTool.tool_specs()
